    ns1:inpersonHours "29 horas (37.2%)"@es ;
    ns1:numberOfCredits 3.0 ;
    ns1:otherInformation """The content of the subject may vary depending on the profile of the students, to adapt to the previous knowledge they have acquired.
This subject is related to SDG 7 and SDG 13."""@es ;
    ns1:periodEndingMonth "Junio"@es ;
    ns1:periodStartingMonth "Febrero"@es ;
    ns1:teachingPeriod "2025-26" ;
    ns1:teachingPeriodMonths "Febrero-Junio"@es ;
    ns1:totalHours "29 horas"@es ;
    schema:activitiesWorkload "100%"@es ;
    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description """The objective of the course is to bring the student up to date on the advanced solutions that are available in relation to thermoelectric power plants in all their versions. These solutions are aimed at improving the performance of the plants, the best use of various types of fuels and resources, and the reduction of their environmental impact, controlling/eliminating emissions of greenhouse gases and other types of emissions. Hybridization with other thermal technologies, such as biomass or solar, is also considered and discussed. The student will prepare to work professionally in high-level positions in companies in the energy sector related to
with the engineering of thermal power plants. Among other things, the student will be able to understand the decarbonization technologies applicable to thermal power plants and carry out comparative studies of the different types of thermal power plants. Additionally, professional and innovation leadership is explored by taking part in business idea competitions in the energy sector."""@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/alberto.abanades%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Inglés/Castellano"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/alberto.abanades%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Advanced Thermal Plants"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/CB7> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CB7" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Que los estudiantes sepan aplicar los conocimientos adquiridos y su capacidad de resolución de problemas en entornos nuevos o poco conocidos dentro de contextos más amplios (o multidisciplinares) relacionados con su área de estudio/ Students are capable of applying their knowledge, understanding, and problem"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/CB9> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CB9" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Que los estudiantes sepan comunicar sus conclusiones y los conocimientos y razones últimas que las sustentan a públicos especializados y no especializados de un modo claro y sin ambigüedades/ Students are capable of clearly and unambiguously communicating their conclusions, and the underlying knowledge and rationale to specialist and non"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/CE11> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE11" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Analizar el comportamiento energético y control de los sistemas de energías renovables determinando y aplicando criterios innovadores de optimización energética, económica y ambiental, aplicando metodologías de diseño, simulación y análisis de los componentes y sistemas de energías renovables: solares, eólicos, hidráulicos, de biomasa, de energías marinas, geotérmicas y otras energías renovables; para contribuir a su desarrollo tecnológico y a su competitividad con otras tecnologías energéticas./ Analyze the energy behavior and control of renewable energy systems determining and applying innovative criteria for energy, economic and environmental optimization, applying design methodologies, simulation and analysis of renewable energy components and systems: solar, wind, hydraulic, biomass of marine, geothermal and other renewable energies; to contribute to its technological development and its competitiveness with other energy technologies."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/CE12> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE12" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Aplicar conocimientos y disponer de habilidades para acometer el diseño, control y análisis de procesos industriales basados en la generación de calor por combustión convencional y avanzada, evaluando los combustibles mejor adaptados a cada aplicación y proponer soluciones razonadas en el empleo de combustibles/ Knowledge and skills to undertake the design, control and analysis of industrial processes based on the generation of heat by conventional and advanced combustion, evaluating the fuels best adapted to each application and proposing reasoned solutions in the use of fuels"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/CE8> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE8" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Disponer de habilidades, criterios y conocimientos para investigar, desarrollar e innovar en el campo de la energía: tecnologías renovables y no renovables, almacenamiento, vectores energéticos, en un contexto de decarbonización del sistema./ Skills, criteria and knowledge to research, develop and innovate in the field of energy: renewable and non"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/CE9> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE9" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Disponer de criterios y herramientas para entender la composición y características de los diferentes tipos de combustibles convencionales y no convencionales./ Skills, criteria and knowledge to research, develop and innovate in the field of energy: renewable and non"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/CG1> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG1" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Aplicar conocimientos de ciencias y tecnologías avanzadas a la práctica profesional o investigadora de la Ingeniería Energética./ Apply knowledge of advanced science and technology to the professional or research practice of Energy Engineering."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/CG5> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG5" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Comprender el impacto de la Ingeniería Energética en el medio ambiente, el desarrollo sostenible de la sociedad y la importancia de trabajar en un entorno profesional y responsable./ Understand the impact of Energy Engineering on the environment, the sustainable development of society and the importance of working in a professional and responsible environment."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/CG8> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG8" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Incorporar nuevas tecnologías y herramientas avanzadas de la Ingeniería Energética en sus actividades profesionales o investigadoras./ Incorporate new technologies and advanced tools of Energy Engineering in their professional or research activities."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/CT12> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT12" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Es bilingüe. Capacidad de trabajar en un entorno bilingüe (inglés/español). / Bilingual. Ability to work in a bilingual environment (English / Spanish)."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/CT13> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT13" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Planifica. Organización y planificación en el ámbito de la empresa, y otras instituciones y organizaciones de proyectos y equipos humanos./ Plan. Organization and planning in the field of the company, and other institutions and organizations of projects and human teams."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/CT14> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT14" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Idea. Creatividad./ Idea. Creativity."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/CT8> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT8" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Entiende los impactos. Educación amplia necesaria para entender el impacto de las soluciones ingenieriles en un contexto social global./ Understand the impacts. Broad education to understand the impact of engineering solutions in a global social context."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/RA63> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA63" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Conocimiento y habilidades de cálculo y diseño de centrales térmicas convencionales y renovables."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/RA64> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA64" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Conocimientos y habilidades de cálculo y diseño de tecnologías de centrales híbridas fósil"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/RA65> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA65" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Conocimiento de tecnologías aplicadas a la decarbonización de centrales térmicas."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/didactic_resource/1> a ns1:DidacticResource ;
    ns1:bibliographyDescription """Xingrang Liu, Ramesh Bansa, Thermal Power Plants: Modeling, Control, and Efficiency Improvement, CRC Press, 2016
Dipak Sarkar, Thermal Power Plant: Design and Operation, 2015"""@es ;
    ns1:bibliographyTitle "Book"@es ;
    ns1:bibliographyType "Bibliografía"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """The evaluation is carried out through a case study, sometimes linked to a problem provided by companies. The work is done in groups, and is evaluated by presentation and writing, with differentiated roles among students.
It is necessary to meet the teaching objectives and the learning results a minimum attendance of 70% of the classes, since many activities are in teams and in case studies. On the contrary, it will be an evaluation examination at the end of the academic period to be averaged with the case study.
The evaluation is fundamentally progressive, derived from class work. Extraordinary recoveries may be based on reasoned written tests on the activities that have been carried out in class."""@es ;
    ns1:hasEvaluationTrial <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002061/2025-26/evaluation/trial1>,
